  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting Independent Media for Effective Development (PRIMED)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting Independent Media for Effective Development is a 4-year global consortium programme led by BBC Media Action and designed to address the commerical and sectoral challenges facing independent media in many developing countries. Primary implementation will be in Bangladesh, Sierra Leone and Ethiopia with learning drawn from a range of contexts. The intended impact of the programme is: Strengthened ability of independent media in developing countries to produce free, independent public interest journalism and provide a fora for constructive public debate both online and offline.</narrative>
  </description>
